# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STAR-LINK Environment Variables Reference
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values before running.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Database (Required)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Neon serverless PostgreSQL connection string.
# Format: postgres://user:password@host:5432/database?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/database

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Application (Optional)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Public-facing base URL of the deployment.
# Used for absolute links in emails, reports, and social meta.
# Omit trailing slash.
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-domain.example

# Contact email shown on legal/compliance pages.
# If unset, the Terms page renders a generic instruction.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTACT_EMAIL=contact@your-domain.example

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# File Storage (Optional)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Vercel Blob store token — required only if you migrate document
# storage from PostgreSQL bytea columns to Vercel Blob.
# Generate at: https://vercel.com/dashboard → Storage → Blob
BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auth Integration (Optional)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# NextAuth v5 secret — required if you enable the NextAuth OAuth
# integration (currently installed but not active by default).
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
AUTH_SECRET=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Runtime Behaviour Notes
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# NODE_ENV
#   Set automatically by Next.js ('development' | 'production').
#   When 'production', the application enables:
#     - Strict-Transport-Security header (HSTS, max-age 63072000)
#     - Secure flag on the session cookie
#
# Rate Limiting
#   The built-in rate limiter uses an in-process memory store.
#   It is effective in long-lived server processes but NOT across
#   separate serverless function invocations (e.g. Vercel).
#   For distributed rate limiting, configure an Upstash Redis
#   instance and replace src/lib/rate-limit.ts accordingly.
#
# Session
#   Sessions are stored in the auth_sessions PostgreSQL table.
#   TTL is 30 days. Expired sessions are cleaned up passively.
#   Run a periodic job or cron to DELETE FROM auth_sessions
#   WHERE expires_at < NOW() to keep the table compact.
